rses if already enrolled in ROTC  successfully passing the Army Physical Fitness Test  a personal interview and observation by the PMS  and on demonstrated motivation towards an Army career   Green to Gold applicants  in addition to the requirements above  must have completed two years of active duty prior to discharge and three months of service for every month of specialized training received  Applicants need a score of 180 or higher with a minimum to 60 points in each event on the Army Physical Readiness Test  a cumulative GPA of 2 5 on a 4 0 scale for all previous college work  a FT score of 110 or higher  and other selection criteria as prescribed by regulation  SAT ACT minimum not required to apply for a two year scholarship  Guardsman or Reservists  or outstanding students who are interested in joining the National Guard or Reserve may be eligible for a two year Reserve Forces Duty or a Dedicated National Guard scholarship  They must have successfully completed two years of college to apply  Contact the Professor of Military Science at the college you are attending or plan to attend to find out more  For more information contact  Maj  Lloyd Wells Phone   540  464 7818 Email  wellsld10 vmi edu  Mr Thomas Atkinson Phone   540  464 7680 Email  atkinsonte vmi edu ROTC Leadership Courses Info for Current Cadets Info for Prospective Cadets Army ROTC Course Information Scholarship Opportunities Benefits Service Obligation Scholarship Requirements Army Reserve Army National Guard Partnership Schools Battalion History Army ROTC Awards Battalion Photo Gallery Army Links Faculty Mr  Thomas Atkinson Recruiting Operation Officer of Army ROTC P   540  464 7680 Main Office P   540  464 7351 F   540  464 7639 Virginia Military Institute 2020 Kilbourne Hall Lexington  VA  24450 Contact Army ROTC  ROTC Leadership Courses Info for Current Cadets Info for Prospective Cadets Army ROTC Course Information Scholarship Opportunities Benefits Service Obligation Scholarship Requirement